[BoardVersionToken "b847ca9bb06fd51a6a492754aff575fa366198c52ff0c50cf654062a4cc36b32"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/basic_major"]
[Student "S"]
{EAST has 17 points counting 1 extra for the fifth \S. This is a middle-range hand with five \Ss. 
So he opens 1\S.

WEST only has 7 points, 6 in high cards and one more for the doubleton \D. 
But she does have three \Ss, so she can respond 2\S.

Since EAST is middle-range, he makes one more try by bidding 3\S.

If WEST had 9 or 10 points she would now bid 4\S - but with 7 she passes.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "N"]
[Vulnerable "None"]
[Deal "N:Q75.KJ74.J942.J8 T.AQT52.853.K762 AJ9642.83.A6.Q54 K83.96.KQT7.AT93"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "2S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "N"]
pass pass 1S pass 2S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 2, nRot: 0, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "c1874ece9b8609caa5152ee37bf3e3158f32d145395e08c31b182144b2947a70"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/basic_major"]
[Student "S"]
{With 8 points, NORTH is not strong enough to open the bidding.

SOUTH has 13 points, barely meeting the minimum for a 1-opening. Note that the fifth and 
sixth \S each added 1 point to his count. He opens 1\S.

Although NORTH passed originally, she must respond to SOUTH's opening bid. Since she has 
three \Ss she raises to 2\S.

In light of NORTH's weak response SOUTH passes.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
