[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: W, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:3, nBasis: 2, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "3c9c135f001fa0fc88c1046abde81f935e383cebdc1ce9189c44e7ccca0d9eab"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/basic_major"]
[Student "S"]
{WEST has 17 points and six \Hs. 
This is a mid-range 1\H opening bid.

With 9 points, (1 for the doubleton), EAST raises to 2\H.

WEST's hand is worth one more try. He invites with 3\H.

EAST had a strong 2\H raise, considering that she might 
have only had 6 points. So she carries on to 4\H.}

